  nickname: jhn
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: d0ec49142d5c7c24fb05ee739840cab0, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The Prologue to John\u2019s Gospel"
      title: "The Prologue to John\u2019s Gospel"
      number: 1
      content: ' In the beginning was the Word, and the Word was with God, and the
        Word was God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'This one was in the beginning with God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'All things came into being through him, and apart from him not one
        thing came into being that has come into being. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'In him was life, and the life was the light of humanity.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And the light shines in the darkness, and the darkness did not overcome
        it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'A man came, sent from God, whose name was John. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'This one came for a witness, in order that he could testify about
        the light, so that all would believe through him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'That one was not the light, but came in order that he could testify
        about the light. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The true light, who gives light to every person, was coming into
        the world. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He was in the world, and the world came into being through him, and
        the world did not recognize him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'He came to his own things, and his own people did not receive him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "But as many as received him\u2014to those who believe in his name\u2014he
        gave to them authority to become children of God, "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'who were born not of blood, nor of the will of the flesh, nor of
        the will of a husband, but of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And the Word became flesh and took up residence among us, and we
        saw his glory, glory as of the one and only from the Father, full of grace
        and truth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "John testified about him and cried out, saying, \u201CThis one was
        he about whom I said, \u2018The one who comes after me is ahead of me, because
        he existed before me.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For from his fullness we have all received, and grace after grace. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For the law was given through Moses; grace and truth came about through
        Jesus Christ. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: John the Baptist Testifies to Jesus'
      title: John the Baptist Testifies to Jesus
      number: 18
      content: "No one has seen God at any time; the one and only, God, the one who
        is in the bosom of the Father\u2014that one has made him known. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And this is the testimony of John, when the Jews sent priests and
        Levites from Jerusalem so that they could ask him, \u201CWho are you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And he confessed\u2014and he did not deny, and confessed\u2014\u201CI
        am not the Christ!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And they asked him, \u201CThen who are you? Are you Elijah?\u201D
        And he said, \u201CI am not!\u201D&nbsp;\u201CAre you the Prophet?\u201D
        And he answered, \u201CNo!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then they said to him, \u201CWho are you, so that we can give an
        answer to those who sent us? What do you say about yourself?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "He said, \u201CI am \u2018the voice of one crying out in the wilderness,
        \u201CMake straight the way of the Lord,\u201D&nbsp;\u2019  just as Isaiah
        the prophet said.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: '(And they had been sent from the Pharisees.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And they asked him and said to him, \u201CWhy then are you baptizing,
        if you are not the Christ, nor Elijah, nor the Prophet?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "John answered them, saying, \u201CI baptize with water. In your midst
        stands one whom you do not know\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "the one who comes after me, of whom I am not worthy to untie the
        strap of his sandal!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'These things took place in Bethany on the other side of the Jordan,
        where John was baptizing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "On the next day he saw Jesus coming to him and said, \u201CLook!
        The Lamb of God who takes away the sin of the world! "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "This one is the one about whom I said, \u2018After me is coming a
        man who is ahead of me, because he existed before me.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "And I did not know him, but in order that he could be revealed to
        Israel, because of this I came baptizing with water.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "And John testified, saying, \u201CI have seen the Spirit descending
        like a dove from heaven and remaining upon him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "And I did not know him, but the one who sent me to baptize with water,
        that one said to me, \u2018The one upon whom you see the Spirit descending
        and remaining upon him\u2014this one is the one who baptizes with the Holy
        Spirit.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: "34: Two of John\u2019s Disciples Follow Jesus"
      title: "Two of John\u2019s Disciples Follow Jesus"
      number: 34
      content: 'And I have seen and testify that this one is the Chosen One of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'On the next day again John was standing there, and two of his disciples, '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "and looking at Jesus as he was walking by, he said, \u201CLook! The
        Lamb of God!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'And the two disciples heard him speaking, and they followed Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "And Jesus, turning around and seeing them following him, said to
        them, \u201CWhat do you seek?\u201D And they said to him, \u201CRabbi\u201D
        (which means when translated \u201CTeacher\u201D), \u201Cwhere are you staying?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: Andrew Declares Jesus to be the Messiah'
      title: Andrew Declares Jesus to be the Messiah
      number: 39
      content: "He said to them, \u201CCome and you will see!\u201D So they came
        and saw where he was staying, and they stayed with him that day (it was about
        the tenth hour). "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'Andrew, the brother of Simon Peter, was one of the two who heard
        John and followed him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "This one first found his own brother Simon and said to him, \u201CWe
        have found the Messiah!\u201D (which is translated \u201CChrist\u201D). "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: Jesus Calls Philip and Nathanael'
      title: Jesus Calls Philip and Nathanael
      number: 42
      content: "He brought him to Jesus. Looking at him, Jesus said, \u201CYou are
        Simon the son of John. You will be called Cephas\u201D (which is interpreted
        \u201CPeter\u201D). "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "On the next day he wanted to depart for Galilee, and he found Philip.
        And Jesus said to him, \u201CFollow me!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: '(Now Philip was from Bethsaida, the town of Andrew and Peter.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "Philip found Nathanael and said to him, \u201CWe have found the one
        whom Moses wrote about in the law, and the prophets wrote about\u2014Jesus
        son of Joseph from Nazareth!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "And Nathanael said to him, \u201CCan anything good come out of Nazareth?\u201D
        Philip said to him, \u201CCome and see!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "Jesus saw Nathanael coming toward him and said about him, \u201CLook!
        A true Israelite in whom is no deceit!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "Nathanael said to him, \u201CFrom where do you know me?\u201D Jesus
        answered and said to him, \u201CBefore Philip called you, when you were under
        the fig tree, I saw you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "Nathanael answered him, \u201CRabbi, you are the Son of God! You
        are the king of Israel!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "Jesus answered and said to him, \u201CBecause I said to you that
        I saw you under the fig tree, do you believe? You will see greater things
        than these!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "And he said to him, \u201CTruly, truly I say to all of you, you will
        see heaven opened and the angels of God ascending and descending upon the
        Son of Man.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Wedding at Cana: Water Turned into Wine'
      title: 'The Wedding at Cana: Water Turned into Wine'
      number: 1
      content: ' And on the third day, there was a wedding at Cana in Galilee, and
        the mother of Jesus was there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And both Jesus and his disciples were invited to the wedding. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And when the wine ran out, the mother of Jesus said to him, \u201CThey
        have no wine!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And Jesus said to her, \u201CWhat does your concern have to do with
        me, woman? My hour has not yet come.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "His mother said to the servants, \u201CWhatever he says to you, do
        it!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now six stone water jars were set there, in accordance with the ceremonial
        cleansing of the Jews, each holding two or three measures.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Jesus said to them, \u201CFill the water jars with water.\u201D And
        they filled them to the brim. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And he said to them, \u201CNow draw some out and take it to the head
        steward. So they took it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Now when the head steward tasted the water which had become wine
        and did not know where it was from\u2014but the servants who had drawn the
        water knew\u2014the head steward summoned the bridegroom "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "and said to him, \u201CEveryone serves the good wine first, and whenever
        they are drunk, the inferior. You have kept the good wine until now!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "11: Jesus\u2019 First Journey to Jerusalem"
      title: "Jesus\u2019 First Journey to Jerusalem"
      number: 11
      content: 'This beginning of signs Jesus performed at Cana in Galilee, and revealed
        his glory, and his disciples believed in him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'After this he went down to Capernaum, and his mother and brothers
        and his disciples, and they stayed there a few days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: The Cleansing of the Temple'
      title: The Cleansing of the Temple
      number: 13
      content: 'And the Passover of the Jews was near, and Jesus went up to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And he found in the temple courts those who were selling oxen and
        sheep and doves, and the money changers seated. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And he made a whip of cords and drove them all out of the temple
        courts, both the sheep and the oxen, and he poured out the coins of the money
        changers and overturned their tables. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And to the ones selling the doves he said, \u201CTake these things
        away from here! Do not make my Father\u2019s house a marketplace!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "His disciples remembered that it is written, \u201CZeal for your
        house will consume me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So the Jews answered and said to him, \u201CWhat sign do you show
        to us, because you are doing these things?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Jesus answered and said to them, \u201CDestroy this temple, and in
        three days I will raise it up!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then the Jews said, \u201CThis temple has been under construction
        forty-six years, and will you raise it up in three days?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'But he was speaking about the temple of his body. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Jesus at the Passover'
      title: Jesus at the Passover
      number: 22
      content: 'So when he was raised from the dead, his disciples remembered that
        he had said this, and they believed the scripture and the saying that Jesus
        had spoken. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Now while he was in Jerusalem at the Passover, during the feast,
        many believed in his name because they saw his signs which he was doing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'But Jesus himself did not entrust himself to them, because he knew
        all people,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'and because he did not need anyone to testify about man, for he himself
        knew what was in man.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Meeting with Nicodemus'
      title: A Meeting with Nicodemus
      number: 1
      content: ' Now there was a man of the Pharisees whose name was Nicodemus, a
        ruler of the Jews. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "This man came to him at night and said to him, \u201CRabbi, we know
        that you are a teacher who has come from God, for no one is able to perform
        these signs that you are performing unless God were with him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Jesus answered and said to him, \u201CTruly, truly I say to you,
        unless someone is born from above, he is not able to see the kingdom of God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Nicodemus said to him, \u201CHow can a man be born when he is an
        old man? He is not able to enter into his mother\u2019s womb for the second
        time and be born, can he?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Jesus answered, \u201CTruly, truly I say to you, unless someone is
        born of water and spirit, he is not able to enter into the kingdom of God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'What is born of the flesh is flesh, and what is born of the Spirit
        is spirit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Do not be astonished that I said to you, \u2018It is necessary for
        you to be born from above.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The wind blows wherever it wishes, and you hear the sound of it,
        but you do not know where it comes from and where it is going. So is everyone
        who is born of the Spirit.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Nicodemus answered and said to him, \u201CHow can these things be?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Jesus answered and said to him, \u201CAre you the teacher of Israel,
        and you do not understand these things? "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Truly, truly I say to you, we speak what we know, and we testify
        about what we have seen, and you do not accept our testimony! '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'If I tell you earthly things and you do not believe, how will you
        believe if I tell you heavenly things? '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And no one has ascended into heaven except the one who descended
        from heaven\u2014the Son of Man. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And just as Moses lifted up the snake in the wilderness, thus it
        is necessary that the Son of Man be lifted up, '
      comments: []
    - name: "15: God\u2019s Love for the World"
      title: "God\u2019s Love for the World"
      number: 15
      content: "so that everyone who believes in him will have eternal life.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For in this way God loved the world, so that he gave his one and
        only Son, in order that everyone who believes in him will not perish, but
        will have eternal life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For God did not send his Son into the world in order that he should
        judge the world, but in order that the world should be saved through him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The one who believes in him is not judged, but the one who does not
        believe has already been judged, because he has not believed in the name
        of the one and only Son of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And this is the judgment: that the light has come into the world,
        and people loved the darkness rather than the light, because their deeds
        were evil. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'For everyone who practices evil hates the light and does not come
        to the light, lest his deeds be exposed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Additional Testimony by John the Baptist About Jesus'
      title: Additional Testimony by John the Baptist About Jesus
      number: 21
      content: 'But the one who practices the truth comes to the light, in order
        that his deeds may be revealed, that they are done in God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'After these things Jesus and his disciples came into Judean territory,
        and there he spent time with them and was baptizing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Now John was also baptizing at Aenon near Salim, because water was
        plentiful there, and they were coming and were being baptized. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: '(For John had not yet been thrown into prison.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "So a dispute occurred on the part of John\u2019s disciples with a
        Jew concerning purification. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And they came to John and said to him, \u201CRabbi, he who was with
        you on the other side of the Jordan, about whom you testified\u2014look,
        this one is baptizing, and all are coming to him!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "John answered and said, \u201CA man can receive not one thing unless
        it is granted to him from heaven! "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "You yourselves testify about me that I said, \u2018I am not the Christ,
        but I am sent before that one.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "The one who has the bride is the bridegroom. But the friend of the
        bridegroom, who stands and hears him, rejoices greatly because of the bridegroom\u2019s
        voice. So this joy of mine is complete. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "It is necessary for that one to increase, but for me to decrease.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'The one who comes from above is over all. The one who is from the
        earth is from the earth and speaks from the earth; the one who comes from
        heaven is over all. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'What he has seen and heard, this he testifies, and no one accepts
        his testimony. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'The one who accepts his testimony has attested that God is true. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'For the one whom God sent speaks the words of God, for he does not
        give the Spirit by measure. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'The Father loves the Son and has given all things into his hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "The one who believes in the Son has eternal life, but the one who
        disobeys the Son will not see life\u2014but the wrath of God remains on him.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The Samaritan Woman at Jacob\u2019s Well"
      title: "The Samaritan Woman at Jacob\u2019s Well"
      number: 1
      content: ' Now when Jesus knew that the Pharisees had heard that Jesus was
        making and baptizing more disciples than John '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '(although Jesus himself was not baptizing, but his disciples), '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'he left Judea and departed again for Galilee. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And it was necessary for him to go through Samaria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now he came to a town of Samaria called Sychar, near the piece of
        land that Jacob had given to his son Joseph. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And Jacob\u2019s well was there, so Jesus, because he had become
        tired from the journey, simply sat down at the well. It was about the sixth
        hour. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "A woman of Samaria came to draw water. Jesus said to her, \u201CGive
        me water to drink.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '(For his disciples had gone away into the town so that they could
        buy food.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So the Samaritan woman said to him, \u201CHow do you, being a Jew,
        ask from me water to drink, since I am a Samaritan woman?\u201D (For Jews
        have no dealings with Samaritans.) "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Jesus answered and said to her, \u201CIf you had known the gift of
        God and who it is who says to you, \u2018Give me water to drink,\u2019 you
        would have asked him, and he would have given you living water.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "The woman said to him, \u201CSir, you have no bucket and the well
        is deep! From where then do you get this living water? "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "You are not greater than our father Jacob, are you, who gave us the
        well and drank from it himself, and his sons and his livestock?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Jesus answered and said to her, \u201CEveryone who drinks of this
        water will be thirsty again. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But whoever drinks of this water which I will give to him will never
        be thirsty for eternity, but the water which I will give to him will become
        in him a well of water springing up to eternal life.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "The woman said to him, \u201CSir, give me this water, so that I will
        not be thirsty or come here to draw water!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "He said to her, \u201CGo, call your husband and come here.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "The woman answered and said to him, \u201CI do not have a husband.\u201D
        Jesus said to her, \u201CYou have said rightly, \u2018I do not have a husband,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "for you have had five husbands, and the one whom you have now is
        not your husband; this you have said truthfully!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "The woman said to him, \u201CSir, I see that you are a prophet. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Our fathers worshiped on this mountain, and you people say that in
        Jerusalem is the place where it is necessary to worship.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Jesus said to her, \u201CBelieve me, woman, that an hour is coming
        when neither on this mountain nor in Jerusalem will you worship the Father. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'You worship what you do not know. We worship what we know, because
        salvation is from the Jews. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "But an hour is coming\u2014and now is here\u2014when the true worshipers
        will worship the Father in spirit and truth, for indeed the Father seeks
        such people to be his worshipers. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "God is spirit, and the ones who worship him must worship in spirit
        and truth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "The woman said to him, \u201CI know that Messiah is coming\u201D
        (the one called Christ); \u201Cwhenever that one comes, he will proclaim
        all things to us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: The Disciples and the Harvest'
      title: The Disciples and the Harvest
      number: 26
      content: "Jesus said to her, \u201CI, the one speaking to you, am he.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And at this point his disciples came, and they were astonished that
        he was speaking with a woman. However, no one said, \u201CWhat do you seek?\u201D
        or \u201CWhy are you speaking with her?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'So the woman left her water jar and went away into the town and said
        to the people,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CCome, see a man who told me everything I have ever done! Perhaps
        this one is the Christ?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'They went out from the town and were coming to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "In the meanwhile the disciples were asking him, saying, \u201CRabbi,
        eat something!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "But he said to them, \u201CI have food to eat that you do not know
        about.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "So the disciples began to say to one another, \u201CNo one brought
        him anything to eat, did they?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Jesus said to them, \u201CMy food is that I do the will of the one
        who sent me and complete his work. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Do you not say, \u2018There are yet four months and the harvest comes\u2019?
        Behold, I say to you, lift up your eyes and look at the fields, that they
        are white for harvest already.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'The one who reaps receives wages and gathers fruit for eternal life,
        in order that the one who sows and the one who reaps can rejoice together. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "For in this instance the saying is true, \u2018It is one who sows
        and another who reaps.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: The Samaritans and the Savior of the World'
      title: The Samaritans and the Savior of the World
      number: 38
      content: "I sent you to reap what you did not work for; others have worked,
        and you have entered into their work.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "Now from that town many of the Samaritans believed in him because
        of the word of the woman who testified, \u201CHe told me everything that
        I have done.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'So when the Samaritans came to him, they began asking him to stay
        with them. And he stayed there two days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'And many more believed because of his word, '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: Return to Galilee'
      title: Return to Galilee
      number: 42
      content: "And they were saying to the woman, \u201CNo longer because of what
        you said do we believe, for we ourselves have heard, and we know that this
        one is truly the Savior of the world!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'And after the two days he departed from there into Galilee. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'For Jesus himself testified that a prophet has no honor in his own
        homeland. '
      comments: []
    - name: "45: A Royal Official\u2019s Son Is Healed"
      title: "A Royal Official\u2019s Son Is Healed"
      number: 45
      content: 'So when he came to Galilee, the Galileans welcomed him, because they
        had seen all the things he had done in Jerusalem at the feast (for they themselves
        had also come to the feast). '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'Now he came again to Cana in Galilee, where he had made the water
        wine. And there was at Capernaum a certain royal official whose son was sick. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'This man, when he heard that Jesus had come from Judea into Galilee,
        went to him and asked that he come down and heal his son, for he was about
        to die. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "So Jesus said to him, \u201CUnless you people see signs and wonders,
        you will never believe!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "The royal official said to him, \u201CSir, come down before my child
        dies!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "Jesus said to him, \u201CGo, your son will live.\u201D The man believed
        the word that Jesus spoke to him, and he departed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'Now as he was going down, his slaves met him, saying that his child
        was alive. '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: "So he inquired from them the hour at which he had gotten better.
        Then they said to him, \u201CYesterday at the seventh hour the fever left
        him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: "So the father knew that it was that same hour at which Jesus said
        to him, \u201CYour son will live,\u201D and he himself believed, and his
        whole household. "
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'Now this is again a second sign Jesus performed when he came from
        Judea into Galilee. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Paralytic Is Healed'
      title: A Paralytic Is Healed
      number: 1
      content: ' After these things there was a feast of the Jews, and Jesus went
        up to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Now there is in Jerusalem near the Sheep Gate a pool called in Aramaic
        Bethzatha, which has five porticoes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'In these were lying a large number of those who were sick, blind,
        lame, paralyzed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And a certain man was there who had been thirty-eight years in his
        sickness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Jesus, when he saw this one lying there and knew that he had been
        sick a long time already, said to him, \u201CDo you want to become well?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The one who was sick answered him, \u201CSir, I do not have anyone
        that, whenever the water is stirred up, could put me into the pool. But while
        I am coming, another goes down before me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Jesus said to him, \u201CGet up! Pick up your mat and walk!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And immediately the man became well and picked up his mat and began
        to walk. (Now it was the Sabbath on that day.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So the Jews were saying to the one who had been healed, \u201CIt
        is the Sabbath, and it is not permitted for you to pick up the mat!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But he answered them, \u201CThe one who made me well\u2014that one
        said to me, \u2018Pick up your mat and walk!\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So they asked him, \u201CWho is the man who said to you, \u2018Pick
        up your mat and walk?\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Equal with God'
      title: Equal with God
      number: 13
      content: 'But the one who was healed did not know who it was, for Jesus had
        withdrawn while a crowd was in the place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "After these things Jesus found him at the temple and said to him,
        \u201CLook, you have become well! Sin no longer, lest something worse happen
        to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The man went and reported to the Jews that Jesus was the one who
        made him well. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And on account of this the Jews began to persecute Jesus, because
        he was doing these things on the Sabbath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But he answered them, \u201CMy Father is working until now, and I
        am working.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: The Authority of the Son'
      title: The Authority of the Son
      number: 18
      content: 'So on account of this the Jews were seeking even more to kill him,
        because he not only was breaking the Sabbath, but also was calling God his
        own Father, thus making himself equal with God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "So Jesus answered and said to them, \u201CTruly, truly I say to you,
        the Son can do nothing from himself except what he sees the Father doing.
        For whatever that one does, these things also the Son does likewise. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'For the Father loves the Son and shows him everything that he himself
        is doing. And greater works than these he will show him, so that you will
        be astonished. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'For just as the Father raises the dead and makes them alive, thus
        also the Son makes alive whomever he wishes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For the Father does not judge anyone, but he has given all judgment
        to the Son, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'in order that all people will honor the Son, just as they honor the
        Father. The one who does not honor the Son does not honor the Father who
        sent him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Truly, truly I say to you that the one who hears my word and who
        believes the one who sent me has eternal life, and does not come into judgment,
        but has passed from death into life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CTruly, truly I say to you, that an hour is coming\u2014and
        now is here\u2014when the dead will hear the voice of the Son of God, and
        the ones who hear will live. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'For just as the Father has life in himself, thus also he has granted
        to the Son to have life in himself. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And he has granted him authority to carry out judgment, because he
        is the Son of Man. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CDo not be astonished at this, because an hour is coming in
        which all those in the tombs will hear his voice "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "and they will come out\u2014those who have done good things to a
        resurrection of life, but those who have practiced evil things to a resurrection
        of judgment. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: Further Testimony About the Son'
      title: Further Testimony About the Son
      number: 30
      content: 'I am able to do nothing from myself. Just as I hear, I judge, and
        my judgment is just, because I do not seek my own will, but the will of the
        one who sent me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CIf I testify about myself, my testimony is not true. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'There is another who testifies about me, and I know that the testimony
        which he testifies about me is true. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'You have sent to John and he has testified to the truth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: '(And I do not receive testimony from people, but I say these things
        in order that you may be saved.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'That one was the lamp which was burning and shining, and you wanted
        to rejoice for an hour in his light. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "\u201CBut I have a testimony greater than John\u2019s, for the works
        which the Father has given to me that I should complete them\u2014the very
        works which I am doing\u2014these testify about me, that the Father has sent
        me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'And the Father who sent me, that one has testified about me. You
        have neither heard his voice at any time nor seen his form. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'And you do not have his word residing in yourselves, because the
        one whom that one sent, in this one you do not believe. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'You search the scriptures because you think that you have eternal
        life in them, and it is these that testify about me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'And you are not willing to come to me so that you may have life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "\u201CI do not accept glory from people, "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'but I know you, that you do not have the love of God in yourselves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "I have come in my Father\u2019s name, and you do not accept me. If
        another should come in his own name, you would accept that one! "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'How are you able to believe, if you accept glory from one another,
        and do not seek the glory which is from the only God? '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'Do not think that I will accuse you before the Father! The one who
        accuses you is Moses, in whom you have put your hope! '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'For if you had believed Moses, you would believe me, for that one
        wrote about me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "But if you do not believe that one\u2019s writings, how will you
        believe my words?\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Feeding of Five Thousand'
      title: The Feeding of Five Thousand
      number: 1
      content: ' After these things Jesus went away to the other side of the sea
        of Galilee (that is, Tiberias). '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And a large crowd was following him because they were observing the
        signs that he was doing on those who were sick. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So Jesus went up on the mountain and sat down there with his disciples. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '(Now the Passover, the feast of the Jews, was near.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Jesus, when he looked up   and saw that a large crowd was coming
        to him, said to Philip, \u201CWhere can we buy bread so that these people
        can eat?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '(Now he said this to test him, because he knew what he was going
        to do.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Philip replied to him, \u201CTwo hundred denarii worth of bread would
        not be enough for them, in order that each one could receive a little.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'One of his disciples, Andrew the brother of Simon Peter, said to
        him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CHere is a boy who has five barley loaves and two fish, but
        what are these for so many people?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Jesus said, \u201CMake the people recline.\u201D (Now there was a
        lot of grass in the place.) So the men reclined, approximately five thousand
        in number. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then Jesus took the bread, and after he had given thanks, he distributed
        it to those who were reclining\u2014likewise also of the fish, as much as
        they wanted. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And when they were satisfied, he said to his disciples, \u201CGather
        the remaining fragments so that nothing is lost.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So they gathered them, and filled twelve baskets with fragments from
        the five barley loaves which were left over by those who had eaten. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Now when the people saw the sign that he performed, they began to
        say, \u201CThis one is truly the Prophet who is to come into the world!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Jesus Walks on the Water'
      title: Jesus Walks on the Water
      number: 15
      content: 'Then Jesus, because he knew that they were about to come and seize
        him in order to make him king, withdrew again up the mountain by himself
        alone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Now when evening came, his disciples went down to the sea. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And getting into a boat, they began to go to the other side of the
        sea, to Capernaum. And it had already become dark, and Jesus had not yet
        come to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And the sea began to be stirred up because a strong wind was blowing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then when they had rowed about twenty-five or thirty stadia, they
        saw Jesus walking on the sea and coming near the boat, and they were afraid. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "But he said to them, \u201CIt is I! Do not be afraid!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Discourse About the Bread of Life'
      title: Discourse About the Bread of Life
      number: 21
      content: 'So they were wanting to take him into the boat, and immediately the
        boat came to the land to which they were going. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'On the next day, the crowd that was on the other side of the sea
        saw that other boats were not there (except one), and that Jesus had not
        entered with his disciples into the boat, but his disciples had departed
        alone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Other boats from Tiberias came near the place where they had eaten
        the bread after the Lord had given thanks. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'So when the crowd saw that Jesus was not there, nor his disciples,
        they themselves got into the boats and came to Capernaum seeking Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And when they found him on the other side of the sea, they said to
        him, \u201CRabbi, when did you get here?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Jesus replied to them and said, \u201CTruly, truly I say to you,
        you seek me not because you saw signs, but because you ate of the loaves
        and were satisfied! "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Do not work for the food that perishes, but the food that remains
        to eternal life, which the Son of Man will give to you. For God the Father
        has set his seal on this one.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "So they said to him, \u201CWhat shall we do that we can accomplish
        the works of God?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Jesus answered and said to them, \u201CThis is the work of God: that
        you believe in the one whom that one sent.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "So they said to him, \u201CThen what sign will you perform, so that
        we can see it and believe you? What will you do? "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Our fathers ate the manna in the wilderness, just as it is written,
        \u2018He gave them bread from heaven to eat.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Then Jesus said to them, \u201CTruly, truly I say to you, Moses did
        not give you bread from heaven, but my Father is giving you the true bread
        from heaven! "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "For the bread of God is the one who comes down from heaven and gives
        life to the world.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "So they said to him, \u201CSir, always give us this bread!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Jesus said to them, \u201CI am the bread of life. The one who comes
        to me will never be hungry, and the one who believes in me will never be
        thirsty again. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'But I said to you that you have seen me and do not believe. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Everyone whom the Father gives to me will come to me, and the one
        who comes to me I will never throw out, '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'because I have come down from heaven not that I should do my will,
        but the will of the one who sent me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Now this is the will of the one who sent me: that everyone whom he
        has given me, I would not lose any of them, but raise them up on the last
        day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "For this is the will of my Father, that everyone who looks at the
        Son and believes in him would have eternal life, and I will raise him up
        on the last day.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "Now the Jews began to grumble about him because he said, \u201CI
        am the bread that came down from heaven,\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "and they were saying, \u201CIs this one not Jesus the son of Joseph,
        whose father and mother we know? How does he now say, \u2018I have come down
        from heaven\u2019?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "Jesus answered and said to them, \u201CDo not grumble among yourselves!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'No one is able to come to me unless the Father who sent me draws
        him, and I will raise him up on the last day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "It is written in the prophets, \u2018And they will all be taught
        by God.\u2019 Everyone who hears from the Father and learns comes to me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "(Not that anyone has seen the Father except the one who is from God\u2014this
        one has seen the Father.)  "
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'Truly, truly I say to you, the one who believes has eternal life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'I am the bread of life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'Your fathers ate the manna in the wilderness and they died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'This is the bread that comes down from heaven so that someone may
        eat from it and not die. '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "I am the living bread that came down from heaven. If anyone eats
        from this bread, he will live forever. And the bread that I will give for
        the life of the world is my flesh.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: "So the Jews began to quarrel among themselves, saying, \u201CHow
        can this man give us his flesh to eat?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: "Then Jesus said to them, \u201CTruly, truly I say to you, unless
        you eat the flesh of the Son of Man and drink his blood, you do not have
        life in yourselves! "
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'The one who eats my flesh and drinks my blood has eternal life, and
        I will raise him up on the last day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'For my flesh is true food, and my blood is true drink. '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: 'The one who eats my flesh and drinks my blood resides in me and I
        in him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: "Just as the living Father sent me, and I live because of the Father,
        so also the one who eats me\u2014that one will live because of me. "
      comments: []
    - name: "58: Many of Jesus\u2019 Disciples Offended by His Teaching"
      title: "Many of Jesus\u2019 Disciples Offended by His Teaching"
      number: 58
      content: "This is the bread that came down from heaven, not as the fathers
        ate and died. The one who eats this bread will live forever.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: 'He said these things while teaching in the synagogue in Capernaum. '
      comments: []
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: "Thus many of his disciples, when they heard it, said, \u201CThis
        saying is hard! Who can understand it?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '61: '
      title: 
      number: 61
      content: "But Jesus, because he knew within himself that his disciples were
        grumbling about this, said to them, \u201CDoes this cause you to be offended? "
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: 'Then what if you see the Son of Man ascending where he was before? '
      comments: []
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: 'The Spirit is the one who gives life; the flesh profits nothing.
        The words that I have spoken to you are spirit and are life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '64: '
      title: 
      number: 64
      content: "But there are some of you who do not believe.\u201D (For Jesus knew
        from the beginning who they were who did not believe, and who it was who
        would betray him.) "
      comments: []
    - name: "65: Peter\u2019s Confession"
      title: "Peter\u2019s Confession"
      number: 65
      content: "And he said, \u201CBecause of this I said to you that no one can
        come to me unless it has been granted to him by the Father.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '66: '
      title: 
      number: 66
      content: 'For this reason many of his disciples drew back and were not walking
        with him any longer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '67: '
      title: 
      number: 67
      content: "So Jesus said to the twelve, \u201CYou do not want to go away also,
        do you?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '68: '
      title: 
      number: 68
      content: "Simon Peter answered him, \u201CLord, to whom would we go? You have
        the words of eternal life. "
      comments: []
    - name: '69: '
      title: 
      number: 69
      content: "And we have believed, and have come to know, that you are the Holy
        One of God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '70: '
      title: 
      number: 70
      content: "Jesus replied to them, \u201CDid I not choose you, the twelve, and
        one of you is the devil?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '71: '
      title: 
      number: 71
      content: "(Now he was speaking about Judas son of Simon Iscariot, because this
        one\u2014one of the twelve\u2014was going to betray him.) "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jesus\u2019 Brothers Do Not Believe in Him"
      title: "Jesus\u2019 Brothers Do Not Believe in Him"
      number: 1
      content: ' And after these things Jesus was going about in Galilee. For he
        did not want to go about in Judea, because the Jews were seeking to kill
        him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Now the feast of the Jews\u2014the feast of Tabernacles\u2014was
        near. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So his brothers said to him, \u201CDepart from here and go to Judea,
        so that your disciples also can see your works that you are doing. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For no one does anything in secret and yet he himself desires to
        be publicly recognized. If you are doing these things, reveal yourself to
        the world!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Jesus at the Feast of Tabernacles'
      title: Jesus at the Feast of Tabernacles
      number: 5
      content: '(For not even his brothers believed in him.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So Jesus said to them, \u201CMy time has not yet come, but your time
        is always ready. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The world cannot hate you, but it hates me, because I am testifying
        about it, that its deeds are evil. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'You go up to the feast. I am not going up to this feast, because
        my time is not yet completed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And when he had said these things, he remained in Galilee. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But when his brothers had gone up to the feast, then he also went
        up, not openly, but (as it were) in secret. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So the Jews were looking for him at the feast, and were saying, \u201CWhere
        is he?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And there was a lot of grumbling concerning him among the crowds;
        some were saying, \u201CHe is a good man,\u201D but others were saying, \u201CNo,
        but he deceives the crowd.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'However, no one was speaking openly about him for fear of the Jews. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Now when the feast was already half over, Jesus went to the temple
        courts and began to teach.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then the Jews were astonished, saying, \u201CHow does this man possess
        knowledge, because he has not been taught?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So Jesus answered them and said, \u201CMy teaching is not mine, but
        is from the one who sent me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'If anyone wants to do his will, he will know about my teaching, whether
        it is from God or I am speaking from myself. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "The one who speaks from himself seeks his own glory. But the one
        who seeks the glory of the one who sent him\u2014this one is true, and there
        is no unrighteousness in him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Has not Moses given you the law, and none of you carries out the
        law? Why do you seek to kill me?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "The crowd replied, \u201CYou have a demon! Who is seeking to kill
        you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Jesus answered and said to them, \u201CI performed one work, and
        you are all astonished. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Because of this Moses has given you circumcision (not that it is
        from Moses, but from the fathers), and you circumcise a man on the Sabbath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'If a man receives circumcision on the Sabbath so that the law of
        Moses would not be broken, are you angry with me because I made a whole man
        well on the Sabbath? '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: Is Jesus the Christ?'
      title: Is Jesus the Christ?
      number: 24
      content: "Do not judge according to outward appearance, but judge according
        to righteous judgment!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then some of the inhabitants of Jerusalem began to say, \u201CIs
        this not the one whom they are seeking to kill? "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And behold, he is speaking openly and they are saying nothing to
        him! Can it be that the rulers truly know that this man is the Christ? '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Yet we know where this man is from, but the Christ, whenever he comes\u2014no
        one knows where he is from!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then Jesus cried out in the temple courts, teaching and saying, \u201CYou
        both know me and you know where I am from! And I have not come from myself,
        but the one who sent me is true, whom you do not know. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "I know him, because I am from him and he sent me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'So they were seeking to seize him, and no one laid a hand on him,
        because his hour had not yet come. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "But from the crowd many believed in him and were saying, \u201CWhenever
        the Christ comes, he will not perform more signs than this man has done,
        will he?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'The Pharisees heard the crowd murmuring these things about him, and
        the chief priests and the Pharisees sent officers in order to take him into
        custody .  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Then Jesus said, \u201CYet a little time I am with you, and I am
        going to the one who sent me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "You will seek me and will not find me, and where I am, you cannot
        come.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "So the Jews said to one another, \u201CWhere is this one going to
        go, that we will not find him? He is not going to go to the Dispersion among
        the Greeks and teach the Greeks, is he?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: The Promise of the Spirit'
      title: The Promise of the Spirit
      number: 36
      content: "What is this saying that he said, \u2018You will seek me and will
        not find me, and where I am, you cannot come\u2019?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Now on the last day of the feast\u2014the great day\u2014Jesus stood
        and cried out, saying, \u201CIf anyone is thirsty, let him come to me, and
        let him drink, "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "the one who believes in me. Just as the scripture said, \u2018Out
        of his belly will flow rivers of living water.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: Different Opinions About Jesus'
      title: Different Opinions About Jesus
      number: 39
      content: 'Now he said this concerning the Spirit, whom those who believed in
        him were about to receive. For the Spirit was not yet given, because Jesus
        had not yet been glorified.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "Then, when they heard these words, some from the crowd began to say,
        \u201CThis man is truly the Prophet!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "Others were saying, \u201CThis man is the Christ!\u201D But others
        were saying, \u201CNo, for the Christ does not come from Galilee, does he?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "Has not the scripture said that the Christ comes from the descendants
        of David, and from Bethlehem, the village where David was?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'So there was a division in the crowd because of him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'And some of them were wanting to seize him, but no one laid hands
        on him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "So the officers came to the chief priests and Pharisees. And they
        said to them, \u201CWhy did you not bring him?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "The officers replied, \u201CNever has a man spoken like this!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "Then the Pharisees replied to them, \u201CYou have not also been
        deceived, have you?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'None of the rulers or of the Pharisees have believed in him, have
        they?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "But this crowd who does not know the law is accursed!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "Nicodemus, the one who came to him previously\u2014who was one of
        them\u2014said to them, "
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "\u201COur law does not condemn a man unless it first hears from him
        and knows what he is doing, does it?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: "They answered and said to him, \u201CYou are not also from Galilee,
        are you? Investigate and see that a prophet does not arise from Galilee!\u201D
        \u301A"
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'And each one went to his own house.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Woman Caught in Adultery'
      title: A Woman Caught in Adultery
      number: 1
      content: ' But Jesus went to the Mount of Olives. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Now early in the morning he came again to the temple courts. And
        all the people were coming, and he sat down and began to teach them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now the scribes and the Pharisees brought to him a woman caught in
        adultery. And standing her in their midst, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "they said to him, testing him, \u201CTeacher, this woman was caught
        in the very act of committing adultery! "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Now in the law, Moses commanded us to stone such women. So what do
        you say?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '(Now they were saying this to test him, so that they would have an
        occasion to bring charges against him.) But Jesus, bending down, began to
        write with his finger on the ground, taking no notice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And when they persisted in asking him, straightening up he said to
        them, \u201CThe one of you without sin, let him throw the first stone at
        her!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And bending down again, he wrote on the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Now when they heard it, being convicted by their conscience, they
        began to depart, one by one, beginning with the older ones, and Jesus was
        left alone\u2014and the woman who was in their midst. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So Jesus, straightening up and seeing no one except the woman, said
        to her, \u201CWhere are those accusers of yours? Does no one condemn you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Jesus, the Light of the World'
      title: Jesus, the Light of the World
      number: 11
      content: "And she said, \u201CNo one, Lord.\u201D So Jesus said, \u201CNeither
        do I condemn you. Go, and sin no more.\u201D\u301B  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then Jesus spoke to them again, saying, \u201CI am the light of the
        world! The one who follows me will never walk in darkness, but will have
        the light of life.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "So the Pharisees said to him, \u201CYou testify concerning yourself!
        Your testimony is not true.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Jesus answered and said to them, \u201CEven if I testify concerning
        myself, my testimony is true, because I know where I have come from and where
        I am going. But you do not know where I have come from or where I am going. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'You judge according to externals; I do not judge anyone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But even if I judge, my judgment is true, because I am not alone,
        but I and the Father who sent me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And even in your law it is written that the testimony of two men
        is true.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "I am the one who testifies concerning myself, and the Father who
        sent me testifies concerning me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "So they were saying to him, \u201CWhere is your father?\u201D Jesus
        replied, \u201CYou know neither me nor my Father! If you had known me, you
        would have known my Father also.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: Jesus Predicts His Death'
      title: Jesus Predicts His Death
      number: 20
      content: 'He spoke these words by the treasury while teaching in the temple
        courts, and no one seized him, because his hour had not yet come. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "So he said to them again, \u201CI am going away, and you will seek
        me and will die in your sin. Where I am going you cannot come!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then the Jews began to say, \u201CPerhaps he will kill himself, because
        he is saying, \u2018Where I am going you cannot come.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And he said to them, \u201CYou are from below; I am from above. You
        are from this world; I am not from this world. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Thus I said to you that you will die in your sins. For if you do
        not believe that I am he, you will die in your sins.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "So they began to say to him, \u201CWho are you?\u201D Jesus said
        to them, \u201CWhat I have been saying to you from the beginning. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "I have many things to say and to judge concerning you, but the one
        who sent me is true, and the things which I heard from him, these things
        I say to the world.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: '(They did not know that he was speaking to them about the Father.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then Jesus said, \u201CWhen you lift up the Son of Man, then you
        will recognize that I am he, and I do nothing from myself, but just as the
        Father taught me, I say these things. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And the one who sent me is with me. He has not left me alone, because
        I always do the things that are pleasing to him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: The Truth Will Set You Free'
      title: The Truth Will Set You Free
      number: 30
      content: 'While he was saying these things, many believed in him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then Jesus said to those Jews who had believed him, \u201CIf you
        continue in my word you are truly my disciples, "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "and you will know the truth, and the truth will set you free.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "They replied to him, \u201CWe are descendants of Abraham and have
        not been enslaved to anyone at any time. How do you say, \u2018You will become
        free\u2019?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Jesus replied to them, \u201CTruly, truly I say to you, that everyone
        who commits sin is a slave of sin. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And the slave does not remain in the household forever; the son remains
        forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'So if the son sets you free, you will be truly free. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'I know that you are descendants of Abraham. But you are seeking to
        kill me, because my word makes no progress among you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: The Priority of Jesus Over Abraham'
      title: The Priority of Jesus Over Abraham
      number: 38
      content: "I speak the things that I have seen with the Father; so also you
        do the things that you have heard from the Father.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "They answered and said to him, \u201CAbraham is our father!\u201D
        Jesus said to them, \u201CIf you are children of Abraham, do the deeds of
        Abraham! "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'But now you are seeking to kill me, a man who spoke to you the truth
        which I heard from God. This Abraham did not do. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "You are doing the deeds of your father!\u201D They said to him, \u201CWe
        were not born from sexual immorality! We have one father, God!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "Jesus said to them, \u201CIf God were your father, you would love
        me, for I have come forth from God and have come. For I have not come from
        myself, but that one sent me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'Why do you not understand my way of speaking? Because you are not
        able to listen to my message. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'You are of your father the devil, and you want to do the desires
        of your father! That one was a murderer from the beginning, and does not
        stand firm in the truth, because truth is not in him. Whenever he speaks
        the lie, he speaks from his own nature, because he is a liar and the father
        of lies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'But because I am telling the truth, you do not believe me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'Who among you convicts me concerning sin? If I am telling the truth,
        why do you not believe me? '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "The one who is from God listens to the words of God. Because of this
        you do not listen\u2014because you are not of God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "The Jews answered and said to him, \u201CDo we not correctly say
        that you are a Samaritan and have a demon?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "Jesus replied, \u201CI do not have a demon, but I honor my Father,
        and you dishonor me! "
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'But I do not seek my own glory. There is one who seeks and judges! '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "Truly, truly I say to you, if anyone keeps my word, he will never
        experience death forever.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: "The Jews said to him, \u201CNow we know that you have a demon! Abraham
        and the prophets died, and you say, \u2018If anyone keeps my word, he will
        never taste death forever.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: "You are not greater than our father Abraham who died, are you? And
        the prophets died! Who do you make yourself to be?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: "Jesus replied, \u201CIf I glorify myself, my glory is nothing. The
        one who glorifies me is my Father, about whom you say, \u2018He is our God.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'And you have not known him, but I know him. And if I were to say
        that I do not know him, I would be a liar like you! But I know him and I
        keep his word. '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: "Abraham your father rejoiced that he would see my day, and he saw
        it and was glad.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: "So the Jews said to him, \u201CYou are not yet fifty years old, and
        have you seen Abraham?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: "Jesus said to them, \u201CTruly, truly I say to you, before Abraham
        was, I am!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: 'Then they picked up stones in order to throw them at him. But Jesus
        was hidden and went out of the temple courts.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Man Born Blind Is Given Sight'
      title: A Man Born Blind Is Given Sight
      number: 1
      content: ' And as he went away, he saw a man blind from birth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And his disciples asked him, saying, \u201CRabbi, who sinned, this
        man or his parents, that he should be born blind?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Jesus replied, \u201CNeither this man sinned nor his parents, but
        it happened so that the works of God could be revealed in him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'It is necessary for us to do the deeds of the one who sent me while
        it is day; night is coming, when no one can work! '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "While I am in the world, I am the light of the world.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'When he had said these things, he spat on the ground and made clay
        with the saliva, and smeared the clay on his eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And he said to him, \u201CGo, wash in the pool of Siloam\u201D (which
        is translated \u201Csent\u201D). So he went and washed and came back seeing. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then the neighbors and those who saw him previously (because he was
        a beggar) began to say, \u201CIs this man not the one who used to sit and
        beg?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Others were saying, \u201CIt is this man\u201D; others were saying,
        \u201CNo, but he is like him.\u201D That one was saying, \u201CI am he!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So they began to say to him, \u201CHow were your eyes opened?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "He replied, \u201CThe man who is called Jesus made clay and smeared
        it on my eyes and said to me, \u2018Go to Siloam and wash!\u2019 So I went,
        and I washed, and I received sight.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: The Reaction of the Pharisees to the Healing'
      title: The Reaction of the Pharisees to the Healing
      number: 12
      content: "And they said to him, \u201CWhere is that man?\u201D He said, \u201CI
        do not know.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "They brought him\u2014the one formerly blind\u2014to the Pharisees. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '(Now the day on which Jesus made the clay and opened his eyes was
        the Sabbath.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "So the Pharisees also were asking him again how he received sight.
        And he said to them, \u201CHe put clay on my eyes, and I washed, and I see.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So some of the Pharisees were saying, \u201CThis man is not from
        God, because he does not observe the Sabbath!\u201D Others were saying, \u201CHow
        can a man who is a sinner perform such signs?\u201D And there was a division
        among them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So they said to the blind man again, \u201CWhat do you say about
        him, because he opened your eyes?\u201D And he said, \u201CHe is a prophet.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'So the Jews did not believe concerning him that he had been blind
        and received sight, until they summoned the parents of the one who received
        sight. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And they asked them, saying, \u201CIs this man your son, whom you
        say was born blind? Then how does he now see?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "So his parents answered and said, \u201CWe know that this man is
        our son, and that he was born blind. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But how he now sees we do not know, or who opened his eyes we do
        not know. Ask him! He is a mature adult; he will speak for himself!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '(His parents said these things because they were afraid of the Jews,
        for the Jews had already decided that if anyone should confess him to be
        Christ, he would be expelled from the synagogue. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Because of this his parents said, \u201CHe is a mature adult; ask
        him.\u201D) "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "So they summoned the man who had been blind for the second time and
        said to him, \u201CGive glory to God! We know that this man is a sinner!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then that man replied, \u201CWhether he is a sinner I do not know.
        One thing I know\u2014that although I was blind, now I see!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "So they said to him, \u201CWhat did he do to you? How did he open
        your eyes?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "He replied to them, \u201CI told you already and you did not listen!
        Why do you want to hear it again? You do not want to become his disciples
        also, do you?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "They reviled him and said, \u201CYou are his disciple! But we are
        disciples of Moses! "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "We know that God has spoken to Moses, but we do not know where this
        man is from.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "The man answered and said to them, \u201CFor the remarkable thing
        is this, that you do not know where he is from, and he opened my eyes! "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'We know that God does not listen to sinners, but if someone is devout
        and does his will, he listens to this one. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'From time immemorial it has not been heard that someone opened the
        eyes of one born blind. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "If this man were not from God, he would not be able to do anything!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: Jesus as the Son of Man'
      title: Jesus as the Son of Man
      number: 34
      content: "They answered and said to him, \u201CYou were born completely in
        sin, and are you attempting to teach us?\u201D And they threw him out. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Jesus heard that they had thrown him out, and finding him, he said,
        \u201CDo you believe in the Son of Man?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "He answered and said, \u201CAnd who is he, sir, that I may believe
        in him?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Jesus said to him, \u201CYou have both seen him, and he is the one
        who is speaking with you.\u201D \u301A"
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "And he said, \u201CI believe, Lord!\u201D and he worshiped him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "And Jesus said,\u301B \u201CFor judgment I have come into this world,
        so that those who do not see may see, and those who see may become blind!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "Some of the Pharisees who were with him heard these things and said
        to him, \u201CWe are not also blind, are we?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "Jesus said to them, \u201CIf you were blind, you would not have sin.
        But now you say, \u2018We see,\u2019 your sin remains. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus as the Good Shepherd'
      title: Jesus as the Good Shepherd
      number: 1
      content: " \u201CTruly, truly I say to you, the one who does not enter through
        the door into the fold of the sheep, but climbs up at some other place\u2014that
        one is a thief and a robber. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'But the one who enters through the door is the shepherd of the sheep. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For this one the doorkeeper opens, and the sheep hear his voice,
        and he calls his own sheep by name and leads them out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Whenever he sends out all his own, he goes before them, and the sheep
        follow him because they know his voice. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And they will never follow a stranger, but will flee from him, because
        they do not know the voice of strangers.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Jesus told them this parable, but they did not understand what it
        was that he was saying to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then Jesus said to them again, \u201CTruly, truly, I say to you,
        I am the door of the sheep. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'All those who came before me are thieves and robbers, but the sheep
        do not listen to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'I am the door. If anyone enters through me, he will be saved, and
        will come in and will go out and will find pasture. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The thief comes only so that he can steal and kill and destroy; I
        have come so that they may have life, and have it abundantly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CI am the good shepherd. The good shepherd lays down his life
        for the sheep. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "The hired hand, who is not the shepherd, whose own the sheep are
        not, sees the wolf approaching and abandons the sheep and runs away\u2014and
        the wolf seizes them and scatters them\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'because he is a hired hand and he is not concerned about the sheep. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CI am the good shepherd, and I know my own, and my own know
        me, "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'just as the Father knows me and I know the Father, and I lay down
        my life for the sheep. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And I have other sheep which are not from this fold. I must bring
        these also, and they will hear my voice, and they will become one flock\u2014one
        shepherd. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Because of this the Father loves me, because I lay down my life so
        that I may take possession of it again. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "No one takes it from me, but I lay it down voluntarily. I have authority
        to lay it down, and I have authority to take possession of it again. This
        commandment I received from my Father.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Again there was a division among the Jews because of these words. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And many of them were saying, \u201CHe has a demon and is out of
        his mind! Why do you listen to him?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Jesus at the Feast of the Dedication'
      title: Jesus at the Feast of the Dedication
      number: 21
      content: "Others were saying, \u201CThese are not the words of one who is possessed
        by a demon! A demon is not able to open the eyes of the blind, is it?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then the feast of the Dedication took place in Jerusalem. It was
        winter, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'and Jesus was walking in the temple in the Portico of Solomon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "So the Jews surrounded him and began to say to him, \u201CHow long
        will you keep us in suspense? If you are the Christ, tell us plainly!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Jesus answered them, \u201CI told you and you do not believe! The
        deeds that I do in the name of my Father, these testify about me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'But you do not believe, because you are not of my sheep! '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'My sheep listen to my voice, and I know them, and they follow me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And I give them eternal life, and they will never perish forever,
        and no one will seize them out of my hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "My Father, who has given them to me, is greater than all, and no
        one can seize them from the Father\u2019s hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "The Father and I are one.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Then the Jews picked up stones again so that they could stone him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Jesus answered them, \u201CI have shown you many good deeds from
        the Father. For which one of them are you going to stone me?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "The Jews answered him, \u201CWe are not going to stone you concerning
        a good deed, but concerning blasphemy, and because you, although you are
        a man, make yourself to be God!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Jesus answered them, \u201CIs it not written in your law, \u2018I
        said, \u201CYou are gods\u201D&nbsp;\u2019?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "If he called them \u2018gods\u2019 to whom the word of God came\u2014and
        the scripture cannot be broken\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "do you say about he whom the Father set apart and sent into the world,
        \u2018You are blaspheming,\u2019 because I said, \u2018I am the Son of God\u2019? "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'If I do not do the deeds of my Father, do not believe me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "But if I am doing them, even if you do not believe me, believe the
        deeds, so that you may know and understand that the Father is in me and I
        am in the Father.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'So they were seeking again to seize him, and he departed out of their
        hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'And he went away again on the other side of the Jordan, to the place
        where John was baptizing at an earlier time, and he stayed there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "And many came to him and began to say, \u201CJohn performed no sign,
        but everything John said about this man was true!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'And many believed in him there. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Lazarus Dies'
      title: Lazarus Dies
      number: 1
      content: ' Now a certain man was sick, Lazarus from Bethany, the village of
        Mary and her sister Martha. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '(Now it was Mary who anointed the Lord with perfumed oil and wiped
        his feet with her hair, whose brother Lazarus was sick.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So the sisters sent word to him, saying, \u201CLord, behold, the
        one whom you love is sick.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And when he heard it, Jesus said, \u201CThis sickness is not to death,
        but for the glory of God, in order that the Son of God may be glorified through
        it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '(Now Jesus loved Martha and her sister and Lazarus.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So when he heard that he was sick, then he remained in the place
        where he was two days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then after this he said to the disciples, \u201CLet us go to Judea
        again.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The disciples said to him, \u201CRabbi, the Jews were seeking just
        now to stone you, and are you going there again?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Jesus replied, Are there not twelve hours in the day? If anyone walks
        around in the daylight, he does not stumble, because he sees the light of
        this world. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But if anyone walks around in the night, he stumbles, because the
        light is not in him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "He said these things, and after this he said to them, \u201COur friend
        Lazarus has fallen asleep, but I am going so that I can awaken him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So the disciples said to him, \u201CLord, if he has fallen asleep,
        he will get well.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '(Now Jesus had been speaking about his death, but they thought that
        he was speaking about real sleep.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "So Jesus then said to them plainly, \u201CLazarus has died, "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "and I am glad for your sake that I was not there, so that you may
        believe. But let us go to him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Jesus the Resurrection and the Life'
      title: Jesus the Resurrection and the Life
      number: 16
      content: "Then Thomas (the one who is called Didymus) said to his fellow disciples,
        \u201CLet us go also, so that we may die with him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So when he arrived, Jesus found he had already been four days in
        the tomb. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '(Now Bethany was near Jerusalem, about fifteen stadia.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So many of the Jews came to Martha and Mary in order to console them
        concerning their brother.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Now Martha, when she heard that Jesus was coming, went to meet him,
        but Mary was sitting in the house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "So Martha said to Jesus, \u201CLord, if you had been here, my brother
        would not have died. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Even now I know that whatever you ask God, God will grant you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Jesus said to her, \u201CYour brother will rise again.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Martha said to him, \u201CI know that he will rise again in the resurrection
        at the last day.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Jesus said to her, \u201CI am the resurrection and the life. The
        one who believes in me, even if he dies, will live, "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "and everyone who lives and believes in me will never die forever.
        Do you believe this?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: Jesus Weeps'
      title: Jesus Weeps
      number: 27
      content: "She said to him, \u201CYes, Lord, I have believed that you are the
        Christ, the Son of God, who comes into the world.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And when she had said this, she went and called her sister Mary privately,
        saying, \u201CThe Teacher is here and is calling for you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'So that one, when she heard it, got up quickly and went to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: '(Now Jesus has not yet come into the village, but was still in the
        place where Martha went to meet him.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "So the Jews who were with her in the house and were consoling her,
        when they saw Mary\u2014that she stood up quickly and went out\u2014followed
        her, because they thought that she was going to the tomb in order to weep
        there. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Then Mary, when she came where Jesus was and saw him, fell at his
        feet, saying to him, \u201CLord, if you had been here, my brother would not
        have died.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Then Jesus, when he saw her weeping and the Jews who came with her
        weeping, was deeply moved in spirit and was troubled within himself. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "And he said, \u201CWhere have you laid him?\u201D They said to him,
        \u201CLord, come and see.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Jesus wept. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "So the Jews were saying, \u201CSee how he loved him!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: Lazarus Is Raised'
      title: Lazarus Is Raised
      number: 37
      content: "But some of them said, \u201CWas not this man who opened the eyes
        of the blind able to do something so that this man also would not have died?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Then Jesus, deeply moved within himself again, came to the tomb.
        Now it was a cave, and a stone was lying on it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "Jesus said, \u201CTake away the stone.\u201D Martha, the sister of
        the one who had died, said to him, \u201CLord, he is stinking already, because
        it has been four days.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "Jesus said to her, \u201CDid I not say to you that if you believed,
        you would see the glory of God?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "So they took away the stone. And Jesus lifted up his eyes above and
        said, \u201CFather, I give thanks to you that you hear me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "And I know that you always hear me, but for the sake of the crowd
        standing around I said it, so that they may believe that you sent me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "And when he had said these things, he cried out with a loud voice,
        \u201CLazarus, come out!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: The Jewish Leaders Plot to Kill Jesus'
      title: The Jewish Leaders Plot to Kill Jesus
      number: 44
      content: "The one who had died came out, his feet and his hands bound with
        strips of cloth, and his face wrapped with a facecloth. Jesus said to them,
        \u201CUntie him and let him go.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'Then many of the Jews who had come with Mary and saw the things which
        he did believed in him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'But some of them went to the Pharisees and told them the things which
        Jesus had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "So the chief priests and the Pharisees called together the Sanhedrin
        and said, \u201CWhat are we doing? For this man is performing many signs! "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "If we allow him to go on in this way, everyone will believe in him,
        and the Romans will come and take away both our place and our nation.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "But a certain one of them, Caiaphas (who was high priest in that
        year), said to them, \u201CYou do not know anything at all! "
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "Nor do you consider that it is profitable for you that one man should
        die for the people, and the whole nation not perish.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: '(Now he did not say this from himself, but being high priest in that
        year, he prophesied that Jesus was going to die for the nation, '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'and not for the nation only, but also that the children of God who
        are scattered would be gathered into one.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'So from that day they resolved that they should kill him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'So Jesus was no longer walking openly among the Jews, but went away
        from there to the region near the wilderness, to a city called Ephraim, and
        there he stayed with the disciples. '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'Now the Passover of the Jews was near, and many went up to Jerusalem
        from the surrounding country before the Passover, so that they could purify
        themselves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: "So they were looking for Jesus, and were speaking with one another
        while standing in the temple courts, \u201CWhat do you think? That he will
        not come to the feast?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: '(Now the chief priests and the Pharisees had given orders that if
        anyone knew where he was, they should report it, in order that they could
        arrest him.) '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus Is Anointed at Bethany'
      title: Jesus Is Anointed at Bethany
      number: 1
      content: ' Then, six days before the Passover, Jesus came to Bethany, where
        Lazarus was, whom Jesus had raised from the dead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So they made him a dinner there, and Martha was serving, but Lazarus
        was one of the ones reclining at table with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then Mary took a pound of ointment of very valuable genuine nard
        and anointed the feet of Jesus, and wiped his feet with her hair. And the
        house was filled with the fragrance of the ointment. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But Judas Iscariot, one of his disciples (the one who was going to
        betray him) said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CWhy was this ointment not sold for three hundred denarii and
        given to the poor?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '(Now he said this not because he was concerned about the poor, but
        because he was a thief, and having the money box, he used to steal what was
        put into it.)  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So Jesus said, \u201CLeave her alone, so that she may keep it for
        the day of my preparation for burial. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: The Decision to Kill Lazarus'
      title: The Decision to Kill Lazarus
      number: 8
      content: "For you have the poor with you always, but you do not always have
        me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Now a large crowd of Jews found out that he was there, and they came,
        not only because of Jesus, but so that they could see Lazarus also, whom
        he raised from the dead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So the chief priests decided that they would kill Lazarus also, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: The Triumphal Entry'
      title: The Triumphal Entry
      number: 11
      content: 'because on account of him many of the Jews were going and believing
        in Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'On the next day the large crowd who had come to the feast, when they
        heard that Jesus was coming to Jerusalem, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "took the branches of palm trees and went out to meet him, and began
        crying out, \u201CHosanna! Blessed is the one who comes in the name of the
        Lord,  even the king of Israel!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So Jesus found a young donkey and sat on it, just as it is written, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CDo not be afraid, daughter of Zion! Behold, your king is coming,
        seated on the foal of a donkey!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '(His disciples did not understand these things at first, but when
        Jesus was glorified, then they remembered that these things had been written
        about him and they did these things to him.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So the crowd who was with him when he called Lazarus out of the tomb
        and raised him from the dead were continuing to testify. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Because of this also the crowd went to meet him, for they had heard
        that he had performed this sign. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Greeks Seeking Jesus'
      title: Greeks Seeking Jesus
      number: 19
      content: "So the Pharisees said to one another, \u201CYou see that you are
        accomplishing nothing! Behold, the world has gone after him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Now some Greeks were among those who had gone up in order to worship
        at the feast. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "So these approached Philip, who was from Bethsaida in Galilee, and
        began asking him saying, \u201CSir, we want to see Jesus.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Philip went and told Andrew. Andrew and Philip went and told Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And Jesus answered them, saying, \u201CThe hour has come that the
        Son of Man will be glorified. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Truly, truly I say to you, unless a grain of wheat falls into the
        earth and dies, it remains by itself alone. But if it dies, it bears much
        fruit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The one who loves his life loses it, and the one who hates his life
        in this world preserves it for eternal life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: Jesus Predicts His Death'
      title: Jesus Predicts His Death
      number: 26
      content: 'If anyone serves me, he must follow me, and where I am, there my
        servant will be also. If anyone serves me, the Father will honor him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CNow my soul is troubled, and what shall I say? \u2018Father,
        deliver me from this hour\u2019? But for this reason I have come to this
        hour! "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Father, glorify your name!\u201D Then a voice came from heaven, \u201CI
        have both glorified it, and I will glorify it again.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Now the crowd that stood there and heard it said it had thundered.
        Others were saying, \u201CAn angel has spoken to him!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Jesus answered and said, \u201CThis voice has not happened for my
        sake, but for your sake. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Now is the judgment of this world! Now the ruler of this world will
        be thrown out! '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "And I, when I am lifted up from the earth, will draw all people to
        myself.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: '(Now he said this to indicate by what sort of death he was going
        to die.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Then the crowd replied to him, \u201CWe have heard from the law that
        the Christ remains forever! And how do you say that the Son of Man must be
        lifted up? Who is this Son of Man?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "So Jesus said to them, \u201CYet a little time the light is with
        you! Walk while you have the light, so that the darkness does not overtake
        you! And the one who walks in the darkness does not know where he is going. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: The People Still Refuse to Believe'
      title: The People Still Refuse to Believe
      number: 36
      content: "While you have the light, believe in the light, in order that you
        may become sons of light.\u201D Jesus said these things, and then he went
        away and was hidden from them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'But as many signs as he had performed before them, they did not believe
        in him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "in order that the word of the prophet Isaiah would be fulfilled,
        who said, \u201CLord, who has believed our message? And to whom has the arm
        of the Lord been revealed?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'For this reason they were not able to believe, because again Isaiah
        said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "\u201CHe has blinded their eyes and hardened their hearts, lest they
        see with their eyes and understand with their hearts and turn, and I heal
        them.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Isaiah said these things because he saw his glory, and he spoke about
        him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'Yet despite that, even many of the rulers believed in him, but because
        of the Pharisees they did not confess it, so that they would not be expelled
        from the synagogue. '
      comments: []
    - name: "43: Jesus\u2019 Final Public Appeal"
      title: "Jesus\u2019 Final Public Appeal"
      number: 43
      content: 'For they loved the praise of men more than praise from God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "But Jesus cried out and said, \u201CThe one who believes in me does
        not believe in me, but in the one who sent me, "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'and the one who sees me sees the one who sent me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'I have come as a light into the world, in order that everyone who
        believes in me will not remain in the darkness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'And if anyone hears my words and does not observe them, I will not
        judge him. For I have not come to judge the world, but to save the world. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'The one who rejects me and does not accept my words has one who judges
        him; the word that I have spoken will judge him on the last day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'For I have not spoken from myself, but the Father himself who sent
        me has commanded me what I should say and what I should speak. '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: "And I know that his commandment is eternal life. So the things that
        I say, just as the Father said to me, thus I say.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jesus Washes His Disciples\u2019 Feet"
      title: "Jesus Washes His Disciples\u2019 Feet"
      number: 1
      content: ' Now before the feast of Passover, Jesus, knowing that his hour had
        come that he would depart from this world to the Father, and having loved
        his own in the world, loved them to the end. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And as a dinner was taking place, when the devil had already put
        into the heart of Judas son of Simon Iscariot that he should betray him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'because he knew that the Father had given him all things into his
        hands, and that he had come forth from God and was going away to God, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'he got up from the dinner and took off his outer clothing, and taking
        a towel, tied it around himself. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then he poured water into the washbasin and began to wash the feet
        of the disciples, and to wipe them dry with the towel which he had tied around
        himself.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then he came to Simon Peter. He said to him, \u201CLord, are you
        going to wash my feet?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Jesus answered and said to him, \u201CWhat I am doing you do not
        understand now, but you will understand after these things.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Peter said to him, \u201CYou will never wash my feet forever!\u201D
        Jesus replied to him, \u201CUnless I wash you, you do not have a share with
        me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Simon Peter said to him, \u201CLord, not my feet only, but also my
        hands and my head!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Jesus said to him, \u201CThe one who has bathed only needs to wash
        his feet, but is completely clean. And you are clean, but not all of you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "(For he knew the one who would betray him; because of this he said,
        \u201CNot all of you are clean.\u201D) "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So when he had washed their feet and taken his outer clothing and
        reclined at table again, he said to them, \u201CDo you understand what I
        have done for you? "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "You call me \u2018Teacher\u2019 and \u2018Lord,\u2019 and you speak
        correctly, for I am. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "If then I\u2014your Lord and Teacher\u2014wash your feet, you also
        ought to wash one another\u2019s feet. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'For I have given you an example, that just as I have done for you,
        you also do. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Truly, truly I say to you, a slave is not greater than his master,
        nor a messenger greater than the one who sent him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'If you understand these things, you are blessed if you do them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CI am not speaking about all of you. I know whom I have chosen,
        but in order that the scripture would be fulfilled, \u2018The one who eats
        my bread has lifted up his heel against me.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'From now on I am telling you before it happens, in order that when
        it happens you may believe that I am he.  '
      comments: []
    - name: "20: Jesus Predicts Judas\u2019 Betrayal"
      title: "Jesus Predicts Judas\u2019 Betrayal"
      number: 20
      content: "Truly, truly I say to you, the one who receives anyone I send receives
        me, and the one who receives me receives the one who sent me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "When he had said these things, Jesus was troubled in spirit and testified
        and said, \u201CTruly, truly I say to you that one of you will betray me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The disciples began looking at one another, uncertain about whom
        he was speaking. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "One of his disciples\u2014the one whom Jesus loved\u2014was reclining
        close beside Jesus. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'So Simon Peter gestured for this one to inquire who it was about
        whom he was speaking. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "He leaned back accordingly against Jesus\u2019 chest and said to
        him, \u201CLord, who is it?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Jesus replied, \u201CIt is he to whom I dip the piece of bread and
        give it to him.\u201D Then after dipping the piece of bread, he gave it\uFEFF
        to Judas son of Simon Iscariot. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And after the piece of bread, then Satan entered into him. Then Jesus
        said to him, \u201CWhat you are doing, do quickly!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: '(Now no one of those reclining at table knew for what reason he said
        this to him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "For some were thinking because Judas had the money box, Jesus was
        telling him, \u201CPurchase what we need for the feast,\u201D or that he
        should give something to the poor.) "
      comments: []
    - name: "30: Jesus Predicts Peter\u2019s Denial"
      title: "Jesus Predicts Peter\u2019s Denial"
      number: 30
      content: 'So after he had taken the piece of bread, he went out immediately.
        And it was night. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then, when he had gone out, Jesus said, \u201CNow the Son of Man
        is glorified, and God is glorified in him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'If God is glorified in him, God will also glorify him in himself,
        and will glorify him immediately. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Children, yet a little time I am with you. You will seek me and just
        as I said to the Jews, \u201CWhere I am going you cannot come,\u201D now
        I say also to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "\u201CA new commandment I give to you: that you love one another\u2014just
        as I have loved you, that you also love one another. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "By this everyone will know that you are my disciples\u2014if you
        have love for one another.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Simon Peter said to him, \u201CLord, where are you going?\u201D Jesus
        replied, \u201CWhere I am going you cannot follow me now, but you will follow
        later.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Peter said to him, \u201CLord, why am I not able to follow you now?
        I will lay down my life for you!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "Jesus replied, \u201CWill you lay down your life for me? Truly, truly
        I say to you, the rooster will not crow until you have denied me three times! "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jesus\u2019 Farewell Discourse"
      title: "Jesus\u2019 Farewell Discourse"
      number: 1
      content: " \u201CDo not let your hearts be troubled. You believe in God; believe
        also in me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "In my Father\u2019s house there are many dwelling places; but if
        not, I would have told you, because I am going away to prepare a place for
        you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And if I go and prepare a place for you, I will come again and receive
        you to myself, so that where I am, you may be also. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And you know the way where I am going.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Thomas said to him, \u201CLord, we do not know where you are going.
        How are we able to know the way?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Jesus said to him, \u201CI am the way, and the truth, and the life.
        No one comes to the Father except through me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "If you had known me, you would have known my Father also. From now
        on you know him and have seen him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Philip said to him, \u201CLord, show us the Father, and it is enough
        for us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Jesus said to him, \u201CAm I with you so long a time and you have
        not known me, Philip? The one who has seen me has seen the Father! How can
        you say, \u2018Show us the Father?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Do you not believe that I am in the Father and the Father is in me?
        The words that I say to you I do not speak from myself, but the Father residing
        in me does his works. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Believe me that I am in the Father and the Father is in me; but if
        not, believe because of the works themselves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Truly, truly I say to you, the one who believes in me, the works
        that I am doing he will do also, and he will do greater works than these
        because I am going to the Father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And whatever you ask in my name, I will do this, in order that the
        Father may be glorified in the Son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Jesus Promises the Holy Spirit'
      title: Jesus Promises the Holy Spirit
      number: 14
      content: 'If you ask me anything in my name, I will do it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CIf you love me, you will keep my commandments. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And I will ask the Father, and he will give you another Advocate,
        in order that he may be with you forever\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'the Spirit of truth, whom the world is not able to receive, because
        it does not see him or know him. You know him, because he resides with you
        and will be in you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CI will not leave you as orphans; I am coming to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Yet a little time and the world will see me no longer, but you will
        see me; because I live, you also will live. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'On that day you will know that I am in my Father, and you are in
        me, and I am in you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "The one who has my commandments and keeps them\u2014that one is the
        one who loves me. And the one who loves me will be loved by my Father, and
        I will love him and will reveal myself to him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Judas (not Iscariot) said to him, \u201CLord, why is it that you
        are going to reveal yourself to us and not to the world?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Jesus answered and said to him, \u201CIf anyone loves me he will
        keep my word, and my Father will love him, and we will come to him and will
        take up residence with him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "The one who does not love me does not keep my words, and the word
        that you hear is not mine, but the Father\u2019s who sent me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'These things I have spoken to you while residing with you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "But the Advocate, the Holy Spirit, whom the Father will send in my
        name\u2014that one will teach you all things, and will remind you of everything
        that I said to you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CPeace I leave with you; my peace I give to you\u2014not as
        the world gives, I give to you. Do not let your hearts be troubled, and do
        not let them be afraid. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "You have heard that I said to you, \u2018I am going away, and I am
        coming to you.\u2019 If you loved me, you would have rejoiced that I am going
        to the Father, because the Father is greater than I am. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And now I have told you before it happens, so that when it happens,
        you may believe. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'I will no longer speak much with you, for the ruler of the world
        is coming, and he has no power over me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'But so that the world may know that I love the Father, and just as
        the Father has commanded me, thus I am doing. Get up, let us go from here! '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Vine and the Branches'
      title: The Vine and the Branches
      number: 1
      content: " \u201CI am the true vine, and my Father is the vinedresser. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Every branch that does not bear fruit in me, he removes it, and every
        branch that bears fruit, he prunes it in order that it may bear more fruit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You are already clean because of the word that I have spoken to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Remain in me, and I in you. Just as the branch is not able to bear
        fruit from itself unless it remains in the vine, so neither can you, unless
        you remain in me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CI am the vine; you are the branches. The one who remains in
        me and I in him\u2014this one bears much fruit, for apart from me you are
        not able to do anything. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'If anyone does not remain in me, he is thrown out as a branch, and
        dries up, and they gather them and throw them into the fire, and they are
        burned. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'If you remain in me and my words remain in you, ask whatever you
        want and it will be done for you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'My Father is glorified by this: that you bear much fruit, and prove
        to be my disciples. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CJust as the Father has loved me, I also have loved you. Remain
        in my love. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "If you keep my commandments, you will remain in my love, just as
        I have kept my Father\u2019s commandments and remain in his love. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'I have spoken these things to you in order that my joy may be in
        you, and your joy may be made complete. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'This is my commandment: that you love one another just as I have
        loved you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'No one has greater love than this: that someone lay down his life
        for his friends. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'You are my friends if you do what I command you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'No longer do I call you slaves, because the slave does not know what
        his master is doing. But I have called you friends, because everything that
        I have heard from my Father I have revealed to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'You did not choose me, but I chose you and appointed you that you
        should go and bear fruit, and your fruit should remain, in order that whatever
        you ask the Father in my name he will give you. '
      comments: []
    - name: "17: The World\u2019s Hatred for the Disciples"
      title: "The World\u2019s Hatred for the Disciples"
      number: 17
      content: 'These things I command you: that you love one another. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'If the world hates you, you know that it has hated me before it hated
        you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'If you were of the world, the world would love its own. But because
        you are not of the world, but I chose you out of the world, for this reason
        the world hates you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Remember the word that I said to you: \u2018A slave is not greater
        than his master.\u2019 If they persecuted me, they will also persecute you.
        If they kept my word, they will keep yours also. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'But they will do all these things to you on account of my name, because
        they do not know the one who sent me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'If I had not come and spoken to them, they would not have sin. But
        now they do not have a valid excuse for their sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The one who hates me hates my Father also. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'If I had not done among them the works that no one else did, they
        would not have sin. But now they have both seen and hated both me and my
        Father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "But this happened so that the word that is written in their law would
        be fulfilled, \u2018They hated me without a reason.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CWhen the Advocate comes, whom I will send to you from the Father\u2014the
        Spirit of truth, who proceeds from the Father\u2014that one will testify
        about me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And you also will testify, because you have been with me from the
        beginning. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Persecution of Disciples Predicted'
      title: Persecution of Disciples Predicted
      number: 1
      content: " \u201CI have said these things to you so that you will not fall
        away. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'They will expel you from the synagogue, but an hour is coming that
        everyone who kills you will think they are offering service to God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And they will do these things because they do not know the Father
        or me. '
      comments: []
    - name: "4: Jesus\u2019 Departure and the Coming of the Holy Spirit"
      title: "Jesus\u2019 Departure and the Coming of the Holy Spirit"
      number: 4
      content: "But I have said these things to you so that when their hour comes,
        you may remember that I told you about them. \u201CAnd I have not said these
        things to you from the beginning, because I was with you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "But now I am going away to the one who sent me, and none of you is
        asking me, \u2018Where are you going?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But because I have said these things to you, sorrow has filled your
        hearts. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But I tell you the truth, it is better for you that I go away. For
        if I do not go away, the Advocate will not come to you; but if I go, I will
        send him to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And when he comes, he will convict the world concerning sin and concerning
        righteousness and concerning judgment: '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'concerning sin, because they do not believe in me, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and concerning righteousness, because I am going away to the Father
        and you will see me no more, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'and concerning judgment, because the ruler of this world has been
        condemned. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'I still have many things to say to you, but you are not able to bear
        them now. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But when he\u2014the Spirit of truth\u2014comes, he will guide you
        into all the truth. For he will not speak from himself, but whatever he hears
        he will speak, and he will proclaim to you the things to come. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He will glorify me, because he will take from what is mine and will
        proclaim it to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Jesus Predicts His Return to the Disciples'
      title: Jesus Predicts His Return to the Disciples
      number: 15
      content: 'Everything that the Father has is mine. For this reason I said that
        he takes from what is mine and will proclaim it to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CA little while and you will see me no more, and again a little
        while and you will see me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So some of his disciples said to one another, \u201CWhat is this
        that he is saying to us, \u2018A little while and you will not see me, and
        again a little while and you will see me,\u2019 and \u2018Because I am going
        away to the Father\u2019?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So they kept on saying, \u201CWhat is this that he is saying, \u2018A
        little while\u2019? We do not understand what he is speaking about!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Jesus knew that they were wanting to ask him, and he said to them,
        \u201CAre you deliberating with one another about this\u2014that I said,
        \u2018A little while, and you will not see me, and again a little while and
        you will see me\u2019? "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Truly, truly I say to you, that you will weep and lament, but the
        world will rejoice; you will become sorrowful, but your sorrow will change
        to joy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'A woman, when she gives birth, experiences pain because her hour
        has come. But when her child is born, she no longer remembers the affliction,
        on account of the joy that a human being has been born into the world. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'So you also are experiencing sorrow now, but I will see you again,
        and your hearts will rejoice, and no one will take away your joy from you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And on that day you will ask me nothing. Truly, truly I say to you,
        whatever you ask the Father in my name, he will give you. '
      comments: []
    - name: "24: Jesus\u2019 Victory Over the World"
      title: "Jesus\u2019 Victory Over the World"
      number: 24
      content: 'Until now you have asked nothing in my name. Ask and you will receive,
        so that your joy may be complete. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CI have said these things to you in figurative sayings. An hour
        is coming when I will speak to you in figurative sayings no longer, but I
        will tell you plainly about the Father. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'On that day you will ask in my name, and I do not say to you that
        I will ask the Father on your behalf. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'For the Father himself loves you, because you have loved me and have
        believed that I came from God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "I have gone out from the Father and have come into the world; again,
        I am leaving the world and am going to the Father.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "His disciples said, \u201CBehold, now you are speaking plainly and
        are telling us no figurative saying! "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Now we know that you know everything and do not need for anyone to
        ask you questions. By this we believe that you have come from God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Jesus replied to them, \u201CNow do you believe? "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Behold, an hour is coming\u2014and has come\u2014that you will be
        scattered each one to his own home, and you will leave me alone. And I am
        not alone, because the Father is with me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "I have said these things to you so that in me you may have peace.
        In the world you have affliction, but have courage! I have conquered the
        world.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus Prays to be Glorified'
      title: Jesus Prays to be Glorified
      number: 1
      content: " Jesus said these things, and lifting up his eyes to heaven he said,
        \u201CFather, the hour has come! Glorify your Son, in order that your Son
        may glorify you\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "just as you have given him authority over all flesh, in order that
        he would give eternal life to them\u2014everyone whom you have given him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now this is eternal life: that they know you, the only true God,
        and Jesus Christ, whom you have sent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I have glorified you on earth by completing the work that you have
        given me to do.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Jesus Prays for His Disciples'
      title: Jesus Prays for His Disciples
      number: 5
      content: 'And now, Father, you glorify me at your side with the glory that
        I had at your side before the world existed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CI have revealed your name to the men whom you gave me out of
        the world. They were yours, and you have given them to me, and they have
        kept your word. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now they understand that all the things that you have given me are
        from you, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'because the words that you gave to me I have given to them, and they
        received them and know truly that I have come from you, and they have believed
        that you have sent me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'I am asking on behalf of them. I am not asking on behalf of the world,
        but on behalf of those whom you have given me, because they are yours, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and all my things are yours, and your things are mine, and I have
        been glorified in them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And I am no longer in the world, and they are in the world, and I
        am coming to you. Holy Father, keep them in your name, which you have given
        to me, so that they may be one, just as we are. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'When I was with them, I kept them in your name, which you have given
        to me, and guarded them, and none of them has perished except the son of
        destruction, in order that the scripture would be fulfilled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And now I am coming to you, and I am saying these things in the world
        so that they may have my joy completed in themselves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'I have given them your word, and the world has hated them, because
        they are not of the world just as I am not of the world. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'I do not ask that you take them out of the world, but that you protect
        them from the evil one. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'They are not of the world, just as I am not of the world. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Sanctify them in the truth\u2014your word is truth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Just as you sent me into the world, I also have sent them into the
        world. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Jesus Prays for the Unity of Believers'
      title: Jesus Prays for the Unity of Believers
      number: 19
      content: 'And for them I sanctify myself, so that they themselves also may
        be sanctified in the truth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CAnd I do not ask on behalf of these only, but also on behalf
        of those who believe in me through their word, "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'that they all may be one, just as you, Father, are in me and I am
        in you, that they also may be in us, in order that the world may believe
        that you sent me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And the glory that you have given to me, I have given to them, in
        order that they may be one, just as we are one\u2014"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'I in them, and you in me, in order that they may be completed in
        one, so that the world may know that you sent me, and you have loved them
        just as you have loved me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CFather, those whom you have given to me\u2014I want that those
        also may be with me where I am, in order that they may see my glory that
        you have given me because you loved me before the foundation of the world. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Righteous Father, although the world does not know you, yet I have
        known you, and these men have come to know that you sent me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And I made known to them your name, and will make it known, in order
        that the love with which you loved me may be in them, and I may be in them.\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus Is Betrayed and Arrested'
      title: Jesus Is Betrayed and Arrested
      number: 1
      content: ' When Jesus had said these things, he went out with his disciples
        to the other side of the ravine of the Kidron, where there was a garden into
        which he and his disciples entered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '(Now Judas, the one who betrayed him, also knew about the place,
        because Jesus often gathered there with his disciples.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So Judas, taking the cohort and officers from the chief priests and
        from the Pharisees, came there with lanterns and torches and weapons. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then Jesus, because he knew all the things that were coming upon
        him, went out and said to them, \u201CWho are you looking for?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "They replied to him, \u201CJesus the Nazarene.\u201D He said to them,
        \u201CI am he.\u201D (Now Judas, the one who betrayed him, was also standing
        with them.) "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So when he said to them, \u201CI am he,\u201D they drew back and
        fell to the ground. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then he asked them again, \u201CWho are you looking for?\u201D And
        they said, \u201CJesus the Nazarene.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Jesus replied, \u201CI said to you that I am he! So if you are looking
        for me, let these men go,\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "in order that the word that he had spoken would be fulfilled: \u201CThose
        whom you have given to me\u2014I have not lost anyone of them.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then Simon Peter, who had a sword, drew it and struck the slave of
        the high priest and cut off his right ear. (Now the name of the slave was
        Malchus.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Jesus Taken to Annas'
      title: Jesus Taken to Annas
      number: 11
      content: "So Jesus said to Peter, \u201CPut the sword into its sheath! The
        cup that the Father has given me\u2014shall I not drink it?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then the cohort and the military tribune and the officers of the
        Jews seized Jesus and tied him up, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'and brought him to Annas first, for he was the father-in-law of Caiaphas,
        who was high priest that year. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Peter Denies Jesus the First Time'
      title: Peter Denies Jesus the First Time
      number: 14
      content: '(Now it was Caiaphas who had advised the Jews that it was better
        that one man die for the people.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So Simon Peter and another disciple followed Jesus. (Now that disciple
        was known to the high priest, and entered with Jesus into the courtyard of
        the high priest.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But Peter was standing by the door outside. So the other disciple
        who was known to the high priest went out and spoke to the doorkeeper and
        brought Peter in. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then the female slave who was the doorkeeper said to Peter, \u201CYou
        are not also one of the disciples of this man, are you?\u201D He said, \u201CI
        am not!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Jesus Before Annas'
      title: Jesus Before Annas
      number: 18
      content: '(Now the slaves and the officers were standing there, having made
        a charcoal fire because it was cold, and they were warming themselves. And
        Peter was also standing there with them and warming himself.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So the high priest questioned Jesus about his disciples and about
        his teaching. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Jesus replied to him, \u201CI have spoken openly to the world. I
        always taught in the synagogue and in the temple courts where all the Jews
        assemble, and I have said nothing in secret. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Why are you asking me? Ask those who heard what I have said to them!
        Behold, these people know what I said.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Now when he had said these things, one of the officers who was standing
        by gave a slap in the face to Jesus, saying, \u201CDo you reply to the high
        priest in this way?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Jesus replied to him, \u201CIf I have spoken wrongly, testify about
        what is wrong! But if I have spoken correctly, why do you strike me?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: Peter Denies Jesus the Second and Third Times'
      title: Peter Denies Jesus the Second and Third Times
      number: 24
      content: 'Then Annas sent him, tied up, to Caiaphas the high priest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Now Simon Peter was standing there and warming himself. So they said
        to him, \u201CYou are not also one of his disciples, are you?\u201D He denied
        it and said, \u201CI am not!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "One of the slaves of the high priest, who was related to the one
        whose ear Peter had cut off, said, \u201CDid I not see you in the garden
        with him?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: Jesus Brought Before Pilate'
      title: Jesus Brought Before Pilate
      number: 27
      content: 'So Peter denied it again, and immediately a rooster crowed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then they brought Jesus from Caiaphas to the governor\u2019s residence.
        Now it was early, and they did not enter into the governor\u2019s residence
        so that they would not be defiled, but could eat the Passover. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "So Pilate came outside to them and said, \u201CWhat accusation do
        you bring against this man?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "They answered and said to him, \u201CIf this man were not doing evil,
        we would not have handed him over to you!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "So Pilate said to them, \u201CYou take him and judge him according
        to your law!\u201D The Jews said to him, \u201CIt is not permitted for us
        to kill anyone,\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: Pilate Questions Jesus'
      title: Pilate Questions Jesus
      number: 32
      content: 'in order that the word of Jesus would be fulfilled that he had spoken,
        indicating by what sort of death he was going to die. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Then Pilate entered again into the governor\u2019s residence and
        summoned Jesus and said to him, \u201CAre you the king of the Jews?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "Jesus replied, \u201CDo you say this from yourself, or have others
        said this to you about me?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Pilate replied, \u201CI am not a Jew, am I? Your people and the chief
        priests handed you over to me! What have you done?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Jesus replied, \u201CMy kingdom is not of this world. If my kingdom
        were of this world, my servants would be fighting so that I would not be
        handed over to the Jews. But now my kingdom is not from here.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Then Pilate said to him, \u201CSo then you are a king!\u201D Jesus
        replied, \u201CYou say that I am a king. For this reason I was born, and
        for this reason I have come into the world: in order that I can testify to
        the truth. Everyone who is of the truth hears my voice.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "Pilate said to him, \u201CWhat is truth?\u201D And when he had said
        this, he went out again to the Jews and said to them, \u201CI find no basis
        for an accusation against him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "But it is your custom that I release for you one prisoner at the
        Passover. So do you want me to release for you the king of the Jews?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "Then they shouted again, saying, \u201CNot this man, but Barabbas!\u201D
        (Now Barabbas was a revolutionary.)  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Pilate Attempts to Release Jesus'
      title: Pilate Attempts to Release Jesus
      number: 1
      content: ' So then Pilate took Jesus and had him flogged.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the soldiers wove a crown of thorns and placed it on his head,
        and put a purple robe on him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and were coming up to him and saying, \u201CHail, king of the Jews!\u201D
        and were giving him slaps in the face. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And Pilate came outside again and said to them, \u201CBehold, I am
        bringing him outside to you, so that you will know that I find no basis for
        an accusation against him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Jesus came outside wearing the crown of thorns and the purple
        robe, and he said to them, \u201CBehold the man!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So when they saw him, the chief priests and the officers shouted,
        saying, \u201CCrucify! Crucify!\u201D Pilate said to them, \u201CYou take
        him and crucify him! For I do not find a basis for an accusation against
        him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The Jews replied to him, \u201CWe have a law, and according to the
        law he ought to die, because he made himself out to be the Son of God!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So when Pilate heard this statement, he was even more afraid, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "and he entered into the governor\u2019s residence again and said
        to Jesus, \u201CWhere are you from?\u201D But Jesus did not give him an answer. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So Pilate said to him, \u201CWill you not speak to me? Do you not
        know that I have authority to release you, and I have authority to crucify
        you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Jesus replied to him, \u201CYou would not have any authority over
        me unless it was given to you from above. For this reason the one who handed
        me over to you has greater sin.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "From this point on Pilate was seeking to release him, but the Jews
        shouted, saying, \u201CIf you release this man, you are not a friend of Caesar!
        Everyone who makes himself out to be a king opposes Caesar!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So Pilate, when he heard these words, brought Jesus outside and sat
        down on the judgment seat, in the place called The Stone Pavement (but Gabbatha
        in Aramaic). '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "(Now it was the day of preparation of the Passover; it was about
        the sixth hour.) And he said to the Jews, \u201CBehold your king!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then those shouted, \u201CAway with him! Away with him! Crucify him!\u201D
        Pilate said to them, \u201CShall I crucify your king?\u201D The chief priests
        replied, \u201CWe do not have a king except Caesar!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Jesus Is Crucified'
      title: Jesus Is Crucified
      number: 16
      content: 'So then he handed him over to them in order that he could be crucified.
        So they took Jesus, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'and carrying for himself the cross, he went out to the place called
        The Place of a Skull (which is called Golgotha in Aramaic), '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'where they crucified him, and with him two others, one on each side,
        and Jesus in the middle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And Pilate also wrote a notice and placed it on the cross, and it
        was written: \u201CJesus the Nazarene, the king of the Jews.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So many of the Jews read this notice, because the place where Jesus
        was crucified was near the city. And it was written in Aramaic, in Latin,
        and in Greek. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then the chief priests of the Jews said to Pilate, \u201CDo not write
        \u2018The king of the Jews,\u2019 but, \u2018He said, I am king of the Jews.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Pilate replied, \u201CWhat I have written, I have written.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then the soldiers, when they had crucified Jesus, took his clothing
        and made four shares\u2014for each soldier a share\u2014and the tunic. (Now
        the tunic was seamless, woven from the top in a single piece.)  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "So they said to one another, \u201CLet us not tear it apart, but
        cast lots for it, to see whose it will be,\u201D so that the scripture would
        be fulfilled that says, \u201CThey divided my garments among themselves,
        and for my clothing they cast lots.\u201D  Thus the soldiers did these things. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Now his mother and the sister of his mother, Mary the wife of Clopas,
        and Mary Magdalene were standing near the cross of Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "So Jesus, seeing his mother and the disciple whom he loved standing
        there, said to his mother, \u201CWoman, behold your son!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: Jesus Dies on the Cross'
      title: Jesus Dies on the Cross
      number: 27
      content: "Then he said to the disciple, \u201CBehold your mother!\u201D And
        from that hour the disciple took her into his own home. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "After this, Jesus, knowing that now at last everything was completed,
        in order that the scripture would be fulfilled, said, \u201CI am thirsty.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'A jar full of sour wine was standing there, so they put a sponge
        full of the sour wine on a branch of hyssop and brought it to his mouth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Then when he had received the sour wine, Jesus said, \u201CIt is
        completed,\u201D and bowing his head, he gave up his spirit. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Then the Jews, because it was the day of preparation, so that the
        bodies would not remain on the cross on the Sabbath (for that Sabbath was
        an important day), asked Pilate that their legs could be broken and they
        could be taken away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'So the soldiers came and broke the legs of the first and of the other
        who had been crucified with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'But when they came to Jesus, after they saw he was already dead,
        they did not break his legs. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'But one of the soldiers pierced his side with a spear, and blood
        and water came out immediately. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And the one who has seen it has testified, and his testimony is true,
        and that person knows that he is telling the truth, so that you also may
        believe. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "For these things happened in order that the scripture would be fulfilled:
        \u201CNot a bone of his will be broken.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: Jesus Is Buried'
      title: Jesus Is Buried
      number: 37
      content: "And again another scripture says, \u201CThey will look on the one
        whom they have pierced.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'And after these things, Joseph who was from Arimathea, who was a
        disciple of Jesus (but a secret one for fear of the Jews), asked Pilate that
        he might take away the body of Jesus. And Pilate allowed it, so he came and
        took away his body. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "And Nicodemus\u2014the one who had come to him formerly at night\u2014also
        came, bringing a mixture of myrrh and aloes weighing about a hundred pounds.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "So they took the body of Jesus and wrapped it in strips of linen
        cloth with the fragrant spices, as is the Jews\u2019 custom to prepare for
        burial. "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Now there was a garden at the place where he was crucified, and in
        the garden a new tomb in which no one was yet buried. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'So there, on account of the day of preparation of the Jews, because
        the tomb was close by, they buried Jesus. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus Is Raised'
      title: Jesus Is Raised
      number: 1
      content: ' Now on the first day of the week, Mary Magdalene came to the tomb
        early, while it was still dark, and saw the stone had been taken away from
        the tomb. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "So she ran and came to Simon Peter and to the other disciple whom
        Jesus loved and said to them, \u201CThey have taken away the Lord from the
        tomb and we do not know where they have put him!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then Peter and the other disciple went out and were going to the
        tomb. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And the two were running together, and the other disciple ran ahead,
        faster than Peter, and came to the tomb first. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And bending over to look, he saw the strips of linen cloth lying
        there, though he did not go in. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then Simon Peter also came following him, and he went into the tomb
        and saw the strips of linen cloth lying there, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "and the facecloth that was on his head\u2014not lying with the strips
        of linen cloth, but folded up separately in one place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So then the other disciple who had come to the tomb first also went
        in, and he saw and believed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Jesus Appears to Mary Magdalene'
      title: Jesus Appears to Mary Magdalene
      number: 9
      content: '(For they did not yet know the scripture that it was necessary for
        him to rise from the dead.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then the disciples went away again to their own homes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But Mary stood outside at the tomb, weeping. Then, while she was
        weeping, she bent over to look into the tomb, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and she saw two angels in white, seated one at the head and one at
        the feet where the body of Jesus had been lying. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And they said to her, \u201CWoman, why are you weeping?\u201D She
        said to them, \u201CThey have taken away my Lord, and I do not know where
        they have put him!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'When she had said these things, she turned around and saw Jesus standing
        there, and she did not know that it was Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Jesus said to her, \u201CWoman, why are you weeping? Who are you
        looking for?\u201D She thought that it was the gardener, and said to him,
        \u201CSir, if you have carried him away, tell me where you have put him,
        and I will take him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Jesus said to her, \u201CMary.\u201D She turned around and said to
        him in Aramaic, \u201CRabboni\u201D (which means \u201CTeacher\u201D). "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Jesus said to her, \u201CDo not touch me, for I have not yet ascended
        to the Father. But go to my brothers and tell them, \u2018I am ascending
        to my Father and your Father, and my God and your God.\u2019&nbsp;\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: Jesus Appears to the Disciples'
      title: Jesus Appears to the Disciples
      number: 18
      content: "Mary Magdalene came and announced to the disciples, \u201CI have
        seen the Lord,\u201D and he had said these things to her. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Now when it was evening on that day\u2014the first day of the week\u2014and
        the doors had been shut where the disciples were because of fear of the Jews,
        Jesus came and stood in their midst and said to them, \u201CPeace to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And when he had said this, he showed his hands and his side to them.
        Then the disciples rejoiced when they saw the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "So Jesus said to them again, \u201CPeace to you. As the Father has
        sent me, I also send you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And when he had said this, he breathed on them and said to them,
        \u201CReceive the Holy Spirit. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: Thomas Doubts But Later Believes'
      title: Thomas Doubts But Later Believes
      number: 23
      content: "If you forgive the sins of any, they are forgiven them. If you retain
        the sins of any, they are retained.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Now Thomas, one of the twelve, who was called Didymus, was not with
        them when Jesus came. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "So the other disciples said to him, \u201CWe have seen the Lord!\u201D
        But he said to them, \u201CUnless I see in his hands the mark of the nails,
        and put my finger into the mark of the nails, and put my hand into his side,
        I will never believe!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And after eight days his disciples were again inside, and Thomas
        with them. Although the doors had been shut, Jesus came and stood in their
        midst and said, \u201CPeace to you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Then he said to Thomas, \u201CPlace your finger here and see my hands,
        and place your hand and put it into my side. And do not be unbelieving, but
        believing!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Thomas answered and said to him, \u201CMy Lord and my God!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: Why This Book Was Written'
      title: Why This Book Was Written
      number: 29
      content: "Jesus said to him, \u201CBecause you have seen me, have you believed?
        Blessed are those who have not seen and have believed.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Now Jesus also performed many other signs in the presence of the
        disciples which are not recorded in this book, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'but these things are recorded in order that you may believe that
        Jesus is the Christ, the Son of God, and that by believing you may have life
        in his name. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus Appears to the Disciples in Galilee'
      title: Jesus Appears to the Disciples in Galilee
      number: 1
      content: ' After these things Jesus revealed himself again to the disciples
        by the Sea of Tiberias. Now he revealed himself in this way: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Simon Peter and Thomas (who was called Didymus) and Nathanael from
        Cana in Galilee and the sons of Zebedee and two others of his disciples were
        together. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Simon Peter said to them, \u201CI am going fishing!\u201D They said
        to him, \u201CWe also are coming with you.\u201D They went out and got into
        the boat, and during that night they caught nothing. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now when it was already early morning, Jesus stood on the beach.
        However, the disciples did not know that it was Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So Jesus said to them, \u201CChildren, you do not have any fish to
        eat, do you? They answered him, \u201CNo.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And he said to them, \u201CThrow the net on the right side of the
        boat, and you will find some.\u201D So they threw it, and were no longer
        able to haul it in from the large number of the fish. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then that disciple whom Jesus loved said to Peter, \u201CIt is the
        Lord!\u201D So Simon Peter, when he heard that it was the Lord, tied around
        himself his outer garment (for he was naked) and threw himself into the sea. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But the other disciples came in the boat, dragging the net of fish,
        because they were not far from the land, but about two hundred cubits away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So when they got out on the land, they saw a charcoal fire laid there,
        and a fish lying on it, and bread. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Jesus said to them, \u201CBring some of the fish that you have just
        now caught.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So Simon Peter got into the boat and hauled the net to the land,
        full of large fish\u2014one hundred fifty-three\u2014and although there were
        so many, the net was not torn. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Jesus said to them, \u201CCome, eat breakfast!\u201D But none of
        the disciples dared to ask him, \u201CWho are you?\u201D because they knew
        that it was the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Jesus came and took the bread and gave it to them, and the fish likewise. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Peter Is Restored Three Times'
      title: Peter Is Restored Three Times
      number: 14
      content: 'This was now the third time Jesus was revealed to the disciples after
        he had been raised from the dead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Now when they had eaten breakfast, Jesus said to Simon Peter, \u201CSimon
        son of John, do you love me more than these?\u201D He said to him, \u201CYes,
        Lord, you know that I love you.\u201D He said to him, \u201CFeed my lambs!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "He said to him again a second time, \u201CSimon son of John, do you
        love me?\u201D He said to him, \u201CYes, Lord, you know that I love you.\u201D
        He said to him, \u201CShepherd my sheep!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "He said to him a third time, \u201CSimon son of John, do you love
        me?\u201D Peter was distressed because he said to him a third time, \u201CDo
        you love me?\u201D and he said to him, \u201CLord, you know everything! You
        know that I love you!\u201D Jesus said to him, \u201CFeed my sheep! "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Truly, truly I say to you, when you were young, you tied your clothes
        around yourself and walked wherever you wanted. But when you grow old, you
        will stretch out your hands, and someone else will tie you up and carry you
        where you do not want to go.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Peter and the Other Disciple Jesus Loved'
      title: Peter and the Other Disciple Jesus Loved
      number: 19
      content: "(Now he said this to indicate by what kind of death he would glorify
        God.) And after he had said this, he said to him, \u201CFollow me!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Peter turned and saw the disciple whom Jesus loved following them
        (who also leaned back on his chest at the dinner and said, \u201CLord, who
        is the one betraying you?\u201D) "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "So when he saw this one, Peter said to Jesus, \u201CLord, but what
        about this one?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Jesus said to him, \u201CIf I want him to remain until I come, what
        is that to you? You follow me!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: A Concluding Word of Testimony'
      title: A Concluding Word of Testimony
      number: 23
      content: "So this saying went out to the brothers that that disciple would
        not die. But Jesus did not say to him that he would not die, but \u201CIf
        I want him to remain until I come, what is that to you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'This is the disciple who is testifying about these things, and who
        has written down these things. And we know that his testimony is true. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Now there are also many other things that Jesus did, which\u2014if
        they were written down one after the other\u2014I suppose not even the world
        itself could contain the books that would be written. "
      comments: []
